This is the difference between the rates it charges borrowers and the rates it pays savers. In the old days – when building societies were keen to demonstrate their difference from banks – they emphasised how good they were at keeping this figure down. The building society trade body, the BSA, described this key measure back in 2007 by saying: “Building societies have been improving their efficiency and value, best illustrated by the narrowing of their margins.
